      "content": "City officials hesitate because they are often paralyzed by political expediency and the fear of voter backlash. Implementing congestion pricing requires confronting powerful, entrenched interests, particularly those who benefit from the status quo of free driving. Furthermore, the political will to enforce such a visible fee is often weaker than the scientific consensus supporting its necessity. Therefore, the hesitation is a failure of political courage, not a failure of environmental understanding.",
